= The <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> Congress

  During the vote on the contentious ‘Freedom Law’ in the Reichstag, the dissidents around Treviranus have adhered to a previous agreement with Hugenburg and Westarp to abstain from voting altogether. Much to the dismay of Westarp, Hartwig, Hulser and Lambach have instead released a statement attacking Hugenburg’s actions as party chair and supporting Schiele in his opposition to the ‘Freedom Law’. In response, Hugenburg and his associates have overwhelmingly voted to expel the three renegade deputies and Treviranus from the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>. Following the congress, large numbers of deputies from the <span style="color: #6D5298;">Christian Social</span> and <span style="color: #0087DC;">Young Conservative</span> factions have left the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span in solidarity with those expelled. 
  However, the decision of Schiele and the agrarian wing to remain, as well as Hugenburg’s strong support from the local organisations, has largely limited the scope of this secession from the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span>. 
